title: George Benson - It's Uptown + bonus tracks (1966) Columbia
description:
THE GEORGE BENSON QUARTET - IT'S UPTOWN

01. Clockwise    [4:29]
02. Summertime    [2:25]
03. Ain't That Peculiar    [2:57]
04. Jaguar    [3:00]
05. Willow Weep For Me    [7:49]
06. A Foggy Day    [2:41]
07. Hello Birdie    [4:01]
08. Bullfight    [3:46]
09. Stormy Weather    [2:20]
10. Eternally    [4:06]
11. Myna Bird Blues    [4:37]

Bonus Tracks:

12. J.H. Bossa Nova*    [3:11]
13. Clockwise (alternate take)*    [4:58]
14. Eternally (short version)*    [2:45]
15. Sideman    [4:48]
16. Minor Chant    [3:24]
* previously unreleased

Tracks 1-14:

George Benson - guitar, vocal
Lonnie Smith - organ
Ronnie Cuber - baritone sax
Jimmy Lovelace - drums (on 1, 4-12, 14)
Ray Lucas - drums (on 2-3, 13)
Recorded in 1966

Tracks 15-16:

From the album LONNIE SMITH - FINGER LICKIN' GOOD SOUL ORGAN
Lonnie Smith - organ
George Benson - guitar
Ronnie Cuber - saxophone
Blue Mitchell - trumpet
Charlie Persip - drums
+ Two unidentified percussionists
Recorded in 1967

2001 Sony/Legacy/Columbia
